German Regulator Unhappy With Risk Controls at Banks, FTD Says

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-06-21T06:53:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/german-regulator-unhappy-with-risk-controls-at-banks-ftd-says.html
German financial regulator Bafin may
fine six banks with its lowest ratings because it’s unhappy with
their risk controls,  Financial Times Deutschland  reported,
without saying where it got the information.  Bafin wants at least one of the banks, which the FTD didn’t
identify, to raise its equity capital, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at   acullen8@bloomberg.net  